<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pebble" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pebble</orth> (sometimes spelt <emph>peeble</emph> in O. Edd.; cf. <emph>Pibble</emph>) a small stone, such as may be found and picked up everywhere: <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.254" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 254</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 21</bibl>. <cit><quote>a p. stone:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 11</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 80</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>